    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-03-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="382"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d382">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Meyer</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-03-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1904</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 339.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith the
                    fraudulent naturalization certificate of one Giuseppe Divito and a copy of his
                    application for a passport. The American consul at Naples reports that he <pb
                        facs="0495" n="407" xml:id="pg_407"/> exacted information from Divito to the
                    effect that he had paid a man, whose name he does not remember, $4 to secure the
                    inclosed certificate. It would appear also from the application of Divito that
                    the certificate had been procured by him after a residence of only two years in
                    the United States.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">G. V. L. Meyer.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
